    • Enum Constant Detail

      • STREAM_BEGIN

        public static final UserControl.Type STREAM_BEGIN
        Type: 0 The server sends this event to notify the client that a stream has become functional and can be used for communication. By default, this event is sent on ID 0 after the application connect command is successfully received from the client.

        Event Data: eventData[0] (int) the stream ID of the stream that became functional

      • STREAM_EOF

        public static final UserControl.Type STREAM_EOF
        Type: 1 The server sends this event to notify the client that the playback of data is over as requested on this stream. No more data is sent without issuing additional commands. The client discards the messages received for the stream.

        Event Data: eventData[0]: the ID of thestream on which playback has ended.

      • STREAM_DRY

        public static final UserControl.Type STREAM_DRY
        Type: 2 The server sends this event to notify the client that there is no more data on the stream. If the server does not detect any message for a time period, it can notify the subscribed clients that the stream is dry.

        Event Data: eventData[0]: the stream ID of the dry stream.

      • SET_BUFFER_LENGTH

        public static final UserControl.Type SET_BUFFER_LENGTH
        Type: 3 The client sends this event to inform the server of the buffer size (in milliseconds) that is used to buffer any data coming over a stream. This event is sent before the server starts processing the stream.

        Event Data: eventData[0]: the stream ID and eventData[1]: the buffer length, in milliseconds.

      • STREAM_IS_RECORDED

        public static final UserControl.Type STREAM_IS_RECORDED
        Type: 4 The server sends this event to notify the client that the stream is a recorded stream.

        Event Data: eventData[0]: the stream ID of the recorded stream.

      • PING_REQUEST

        public static final UserControl.Type PING_REQUEST
        Type: 6 The server sends this event to test whether the client is reachable.

        Event Data: eventData[0]: a timestamp representing the local server time when the server dispatched the command.

        The client responds with PING_RESPONSE on receiving PING_REQUEST.

      • PONG_REPLY

        public static final UserControl.Type PONG_REPLY
        Type: 7 The client sends this event to the server in response to the ping request.

        Event Data: eventData[0]: the 4-byte timestamp which was received with the PING_REQUEST.

      • BUFFER_EMPTY

        public static final UserControl.Type BUFFER_EMPTY
        Type: 31 (0x1F)

        This user control type is not specified in any official documentation, but is sent by Flash Media Server 3.5. Thanks to the rtmpdump devs for their explanation:

        Buffer Empty (unofficial name): After the server has sent a complete buffer, and sends this Buffer Empty message, it will wait until the play duration of that buffer has passed before sending a new buffer. The Buffer Ready message will be sent when the new buffer starts.

        (see also: http://repo.or.cz/w/rtmpdump.git/blob/8880d1456b282ee79979adbe7b6a6eb8ad371081:/librtmp/rtmp.c#l2787)

      • BUFFER_READY

        public static final UserControl.Type BUFFER_READY
        Type: 32 (0x20)

        This user control type is not specified in any official documentation, but is sent by Flash Media Server 3.5. Thanks to the rtmpdump devs for their explanation:

        Buffer Ready (unofficial name): After the server has sent a complete buffer, and sends a Buffer Empty message, it will wait until the play duration of that buffer has passed before sending a new buffer. The Buffer Ready message will be sent when the new buffer starts. (There is no BufferReady message for the very first buffer; presumably the Stream Begin message is sufficient for that purpose.)

        (see also: http://repo.or.cz/w/rtmpdump.git/blob/8880d1456b282ee79979adbe7b6a6eb8ad371081:/librtmp/rtmp.c#l2787)
